page.title: 06MANOR FARM
page.content: The farm is owned by Mr Rodgers.Three people work on the farm.The farm has mostly cows but it has a few sheep and some horses.Two dogs live on the farm their names are Bess and Jack.The white cows are slaughtered for beef. The black faced ones make milk.Before the farm was called Manor Farm it was called Luprus Farm.There are 450 hectares of land on the farm. Brimingtons highest point is on the farm.It is 450ft above sea level. There have been no accidents on the farm.The cows are milked twice a day.There are 115 animals on the farm. The horses names are Polo age 8, Jasmin age 6 and Duchess age 10. The farm is on Manor Road.At noon the cows move up the field and gradually move down the field.
